# Cloudflare Pages routing
#
# Blog posts are server-rendered by the Pages Function functions/blog/[slug].js
# at the canonical path /blog/<slug>. (No _redirects entry for /blog/<slug> —
# the function owns that route.)
#
# The original posts used flat /blog-<slug> URLs. 301 them to the canonical
# /blog/<slug> so old links and search-index entries follow through.
/blog-remote-parent-meds       /blog/remote-parent-meds        301
/blog-top-3-chronic-disease    /blog/top-3-chronic-disease     301
/blog-reading-lab-results      /blog/reading-lab-results       301
/blog-inbody-explained         /blog/inbody-explained          301
/blog-ai-and-your-health       /blog/ai-and-your-health        301
/blog-helping-parents-use-app  /blog/helping-parents-use-app   301
